This is not an answer to your question but just genuinely curious. How well do you think 186 prepares someone interested in big data?

history.content: I think it really comes down to which you value more at this point in time - industry experience or data science knowledge. If you feel like you have enough side project/real-world application experience then I don't think you necessarily need CS 169 and would benefit more from taking Data 100. However, if you don't feel like your internship/side project experience is lacking and are looking to land a full-time position immediately following graduation, I'd recommend CS 169 over Data 100. Personally, in these situations I always take the the opportunity to learn more in the field I enjoy, since that's why I chose to study CS in the first place.
